meta_description: Massive government relief passed in response to the COVID-19 pandemic moved millions of Americans out of poverty last year, even as the official poverty rate increased slightly, the Census Bureau reported Tuesday. The supplemental poverty measure was 2.6 percentage points lower than its pre-pandemic level in 2019.
